name: 580775-160 Air Jordan 3 Retro '88 White Cement Restocking
description:
This is the Air Jordan III (3) Retro '88 in the "White Cement" color way. Its been almost 15 years since Jordan Brand became it own subsidiary brand under the Nike umbrella in 1998 and relinquished all uses of the Nike Swoosh or "Air" logo. But now in 2013, JB has already released two models which go back to their roots bearing the logo that gave birth to the Jumpman. The first was the Air Jordan I (1) Retro High OG "Knicks" edition and this AJIII "White Cement" model which features the "Nike Air" logo on the heel counter as well as on the insole and hangtag. This is a retro of the original 1988 Air Jordan III (3) worn by MJ during the 1988 NBA Dunk Contest where he dunked from the free-throw line. If you are a true OG -head or sneakerhead of any sort this pair has become a must have in your collection.

White Cement 3S

name: 308497-089 Air Jordan 4 Bred Black/Cement Grey-Fire Red
description:
This is the Air Jordan Bred 4S, making its triumphant return later this year. Known as the Air Jordan 4 Black Cement, The classic silhouette utilizes black nubuck along the entire upper, while grey works the lace crowns, inner lining, and portions of the sole. Meanwhile, varsity red finishes off the look, all the while adding a bit of pop to the design. Scheduled to be released on November 23rd, the Black Cement 4S Retro would certainly delight many Jordan Brand diehards. There's no doubt that this Black Friday release of the kicks will be a must-cop.

It's going to be an expensive holiday season if you plan on purchasing all of the releases after fall but what ever you do, Make sure you don't pass up on one of the most Iconic colorways in the Air Jordan 4 line. Here at our jordan shoes store you can cop them in advance. Get your own pair Right Now!

name: 378037-010 Air Jordan 11 Bred Black/Varsity Red 2012
description:
The Air Jordan 11 Bred has been one of the most anticipated Retro releases of all time, making it's grand debut this December. OG Jordan heads will remember that it was the Bred colorway of the Jordan 11 that Michael Jordan was wearing when he won his first championship after his first retirement in 1996. Having a release date on December 21st, the shoe is dressed in the Jordan Brand's famous Black / Red colorway. Built from a combination of patent leather and nylon mesh, the high top sneaker sits atop a White midsole and translucent Red outsole. This December, Jordan Brand brings us full circle with the legendary championship-clenching colorway that capped off the greatest season of all time and started a Christmas tradition that keeps the memories as fresh as 1996. name: 136027-108 Air Jordan 5 Grape White/New Emerald-Grape-Ice Blue 2013
description:
A strange fact about the Air Jordan V “Grape” is that it’s so widely popular despite MJ never wearing them in a game. It has no special dunk or game-winner tied to it, but it was one of the first Lifestyle colorways of the Air Jordan Retro to hit the scene and was seen on Jordan’s feet on the cover of the Air Jordan Flight Collection look-book from 1990. Jordan Brand will indeed pair the Grapes with the “Black Grape” version later this year, which stands to be one of the coveted non-OG Retro releases of the year of the V. We’ve got a few weeks before the release date arrives, so check out the official Jordan Brand images below and stay tuned for a release on May 4th.

name: Air Jordan 8 Phoenix Suns Black/Bright Citrus-Cool Grey-Deep Royal Blue
description:
Jordan Brand will be bringing back the Air Jordan 8 models to celebrate Michael Jordan’s 20th anniversary of his first three-peat. The Air Jordan 8 Retro “Phoenix Suns” pays tribute to the 1993 Finals, where MJ and the Bulls earn their first three-peat against the Suns.



The upcoming Air Jordan 8 Retro “Phoenix Suns” features a Black nubuck base with Bright Citrus and Grey accents along with Deep Royal Blue hints. These are set to debut this May 2013 to select Jordan Brand accounts. Let us know if these will be a must-cop when they drop, and keep it locked to Sneaker Bar for more release info.
